      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form assumptions justified by literature or sensitivity analysis; achieved level meets required.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic material model justified for pre-yield regime; bilinear isotropic hardening applied post-yield based on published titanium alloy (Ti-6Al-4V) coupon data. Contact modeled with augmented Lagrangian formulation. Sensitivity of QoIs to friction coefficient (0.1–0.3) showed <3% variation, supporting model form adequacy."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties and geometry inputs traceable to measurements or certified material data; achieved level meets required.",
      "rationale": "Titanium alloy elastic modulus (114 GPa), yield strength (880 MPa), and UTS (950 MPa) sourced from lot-specific coupon testing of the same material batch used in bench specimens. UHMWPE block modulus (0.9 GPa) from supplier datasheet confirmed by independent compression testing. Geometry from calibrated CMM measurements of production screws (n=5)."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test samples representative of production design; achieved level meets required.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested across two independent laboratories. Screws drawn from production lots; dimensional inspection confirmed conformance to drawing tolerances. Inter-laboratory variability in stiffness CV = 4.1%, confirming sample consistency."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
